	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64185605"><p>A couple worthy podcasts from Freakonomis Radio that dig into this:<br>Why Is There So Much Fraud in Academia?<br>Can Academic Fraud Be Stopped?</p><p>Roughly speaking we have an incentive system around "Publish or Perish" that makes honesty much less profitable than fraud.  Fraud itself is too simple of a term when it comes to things like P-hacking.  Until you can have a good career without becoming a paper mill, the problems of low quality and fraudulent academic papers will persist.</p></div>
	</div>

